Dioscorea rotundata

   [942.jpg]
    Authority   Poir.
      Family    Liliopsida:Liliidae:Dioscoreales:Dioscoreaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names white yam, Guinea yam, Igname (Fr)
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 942

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A vine with a cylindrical stem, twining to the right,
   usually spiny and with dark glossy green leaves. Tubers usually weigh
   2-5 kg, on good sites they can be up to 10 kg and 20-25 kg have been
   recorded. USES It is grown for its edible tubers. The tubers are
   however hard and unpalatable if harvested prematurely. GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial vine, tuber reach maturity in 180-300 days from planting.
   COMMON NAMES White yam, White Guinea yam, Guinea yam, Eight months yam,
   Common yam, Eboe yam, Name Guieno blanco, Name blanco. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: D. occidentalis, D. cayenensis. Tubers have a
   definite dormant period. The species is indigenous to West Africa.
   Mentioned as a useful agroforestry species.

   Sources
   SOURCES (Dioscorea rotundata Poir.)
   Tindall H 1983 pp 201-202 & 215-217 [TEMP, RAIN, PHO, TEXT, FER]
   Duke J 1975 pp 15 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 465 [USE]
   Onwueme I 1991 pp 250-266 [TEMP, RAIN, PHO, LIG, FER, TEXT]
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 107 & 108 [RAIN, TEMP, FER, DRA, TEXT]

